00038 Entree& Loi_Etat_rhoT_GP_QC::readOn( Entree& is )
00039 {
00040   Nom expression_;
00041 
00042   Param param(que_suis_je());
00043   param.ajouter("Cp",&Cp_,Param::REQUIRED);//!< XD_ADD_P double Specific heat at constant pressure of the gas Cp.
00044   param.ajouter("Prandtl",&Pr_); //!< XD_ADD_P double Prandtl number of the gas Pr=mu*Cp/lambda
00045   param.ajouter("rho_xyz",&rho_xyz_); //!< XD_ADD_P field_base Defined with a Champ_Fonc_xyz to define a constant rho with time (space dependent)
00046   param.ajouter("rho_t",&expression_); //!< XD_ADD_P chaine Expression of T used to calculate rho. This can lead to a variable rho, both in space and in time.
00047   param.lire_avec_accolades(is);
00048 
00049   if (expression_ == "??" && !rho_xyz_.non_nul())
00050     {
00051       Cerr << "Error in Loi_Etat_rhoT_GP_QC::readOn !" << finl;
00052       Cerr << "The closure equation of rho is not read in your data file !" << finl;
00053       Cerr << "Either use rho_t followed by an expression of T," << finl;
00054       Cerr << "or use rho_xyz followed by a Champ_Fonc_xyz !" << finl;
00055       Process::exit();
00056     }
00057 
00058   if (expression_ != "??")
00059     {
00060       is_exp_ = true;
00061       Cerr << "Parsing the expression " << expression_ << finl;
00062       parser_.setNbVar(1);
00063       parser_.setString(expression_);
00064       parser_.addVar("T");
00065       parser_.parseString();
00066     }
00067   else
00068     assert(rho_xyz_.valeur().que_suis_je() == "Champ_Fonc_xyz" );
00069 
00070   return is;
00071 }

00073 // Method used to initialize rho from a Champ_Fonc_xyz
00074 // In this case the DoubleTab rho_ is initialized and remains constant with time
00075 void Loi_Etat_rhoT_GP_QC::initialiser_rho()
00076 {
00077   int isVDF = 0;
00078   if (le_fluide->masse_volumique().que_suis_je()=="Champ_Fonc_P0_VDF") isVDF = 1;
00079 // We know that mu is always stored on elems
00080   int nb_elems = le_fluide->viscosite_dynamique().valeurs().size();
00081 // The Champ_Don rho_xyz_ is evaluated on elements
00082   assert (rho_xyz_.valeur().valeurs().size() == nb_elems);
00083 
00084   if (isVDF)
00085     {
00086 // Disc VDF => rho_ & rho_xyz_ on elems => we do nothing
00087       rho_.resize(nb_elems, 1);
00088       DoubleTab& fld = rho_xyz_.valeur().valeurs();
00089       for (int i=0; i<nb_elems; i++) rho_(i,0)=fld(i,0);
00090     }
00091   else
00092     {
00093 // Disc VEF => rho on faces ...
00094       int nb_faces =  le_fluide->masse_volumique().valeurs().size(); //!< rho on faces in VEF
00095       rho_.resize(nb_faces, 1);
00096 
00097       Champ_base& ch_rho = le_fluide->masse_volumique();
00098       ch_rho.affecter_(rho_xyz_);
00099       DoubleTab& fld = ch_rho.valeurs();
00100       for (int i = 0; i < nb_faces; i++) rho_(i,0)= fld(i,0);
00101     }
00102 }

00118 // Overload
00119 double Loi_Etat_rhoT_GP_QC::calculer_masse_volumique(double P, double T, int ind) const
00120 {
00121   if (inf_ou_egal(T,-1000))
00122     {
00123       Cerr << finl << "Error, we find a temperature of " << T << " !" << finl;
00124       Cerr << "Either your calculation has diverged or you don't define" << finl;
00125       Cerr << "temperature in Kelvin somewhere in your data file." << finl;
00126       Cerr << "It is mandatory for Quasi compressible model." << finl;
00127       Cerr << "Check your data file." << finl;
00128       Process::exit();
00129     }
00130 
00131   if (is_exp_)
00132     {
00133       parser_.setVar(0,T);
00134       return parser_.eval();
00135     }
00136   else
00137     {
00138 // Initialized from Champ_Fonc_xyz
00139 // dont change, return what is saved in rho_
00140       return rho_(ind,0);
00141     }
00142 }

00164 void Loi_Etat_rhoT_GP_QC::calculer_masse_volumique()
00165 {
00166   const DoubleTab& tab_ICh = le_fluide->inco_chaleur().valeurs();
00167   DoubleTab& tab_rho = le_fluide->masse_volumique().valeurs();
00168   double Pth = le_fluide->pression_th();
00169   int n=tab_rho.size();
00170   for (int som=0 ; som<n ; som++)
00171     {
00172       tab_rho_np1(som) =  calculer_masse_volumique(Pth,tab_ICh(som,0),som);
00173       tab_rho(som,0) = 0.5 * (tab_rho_n(som) + tab_rho_np1(som));
00174     }
00175   tab_rho.echange_espace_virtuel();
00176   tab_rho_np1.echange_espace_virtuel();
